## The Java method

Below is a clean implementation that follows the rules exactly.

```java
/**
 * Scrambles a word by swapping an "A" with the following non-"A" letter,
 * but never reusing any position that has already been swapped.
 *
 * @param word the original word (may be empty or null)
 * @return a new string with the scrambling applied
 */
public static String scrambleWord(String word) {
    if (word == null || word.length() <= 1) {
        return word;                // nothing to scramble
    }

    StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder(word);
    int i = 0;

    while (i < sb.length() - 1) {
        char left  = sb.charAt(i);
        char right = sb.charAt(i + 1);

        if (left == 'A' && right != 'A') {
            // swap the two characters
            sb.setCharAt(i, right);
            sb.setCharAt(i + 1, left);
            i += 2;                 // skip both positions
        } else {
            i++;                    // move to the next pair
        }
    }

    return sb.toString();
}
```

